More Obituaries for Robert Pomeroy


Looking for an obituary for a different person with this name?












Robert Dwight Pomeroy


1920 - 2014
Obituary
Condolences

































 Dec. 3, 1920 - Nov. 9, 2014  Robert Dwight Pomeroy, age 93, passed away peacefully surrounded by his family on Nov. 9, in Woodland, CA. Bob is survived by his daughter, Patricia Pomeroy Eisner married to Charles Eisner of Walnut Creek, CA; and his sons, Robert D. Pomeroy, Jr. married to Susan Backus Pomeroy of Simsbury, CT and J. Richard Pomeroy married to Susan Damron Pomeroy of Woodland. He was predeceased by his wife of 54 years, Mary Morning Pomeroy, who died in 1996. Bob was a proud granddad (GDad) to his seven grandchildren, Daniel Eisner married to Theresa Massagli Eisner, Deborah Eisner Joffe married to Joseph Joffe, Jonathan Eisner, Elizabeth Pomeroy Lipscomb married to Stephen Lipscomb, Sarah Pomeroy Wilson married to Ryan Wilson, Lauren Damron Kiesz married to Christopher Kiesz and Claire Morning Pomeroy Warren married to Matthew Warren. Bob also had six great grandchildren, Olivia and Audrey Kiesz, James and Mason Lipscomb and Leah and Zoe Joffe.  Bobby Dwight Pomeroy, later changed to Robert, was born in Pittsburg (no H), Kansas on Dec. 3, 1920. He moved with his family to Long Beach, CA in 1932 and lived in San Bernardino where he met Mary in 1934. Bob and Mary were high school sweethearts and graduated from San Bernardino High School in 1937 and were active in Christian Endeavor. Bob attended UC Berkeley and graduated from UCLA in 1941 before joining the US Coast Guard. He served as an officer in World War II helping build LORAN stations in the South Pacific. Bob worked his entire career for the Southern California Gas Company retiring as a Vice President in 1985 after 42 years. Bob and Mary raised their family in Glendale, CA and were Elders and Deacons of the Glendale Presbyterian Church. They moved to Woodland in 1989 and were active in the Yolo County History Museum, the Woodland Presbyterian Church and the Woodland Sunrise Rotary Club.  Bob led a life of service through the Presbyterian Church, the Exchange Club of Los Angeles, the Boy Scouts of America, US Coast Guard and Rotary. He and the family loved to travel by car and trailer, air or cruise ship visiting all 50 states and many ports of call. Bob loved crossword puzzles, genealogy, ice cream and baseball, especially the Los Angeles Dodgers.  Services will be private. The family requests that in lieu of flowers donations may be made in memory of Robert D. Pomeroy to St. John's Retirement Village, 135 Woodland Ave. Woodland, CA 95695 or the Rotary Foundation at www.rotary.org.



Published in Daily Democrat from Nov. 12 to Nov. 13, 2014


